<HR> <P>
<H2><A NAME=SECTION00133100000000000000> Translate Operation</A></H2>
<P>
	<A NAME=esc-tr HREF="esc-trbig.gif"><IMG ALIGN=BOTTOM ALT="" SRC="esc-tr.gif"></A>
	<A HREF="esc-trbig.gif">Figure (esc-tr): Translating Cylinder Vertex to (1, 1, 1)</A>
<P>
<tt>mged&gt; <em>Select the ``Translate'' entry in the solid edit menu</em> <BR>mged&gt; <em>p 1 1 1</em> <BR>mged&gt;
</tt>
<P>
The location of the vertex point V is moved to (1, 1, 1).
The locations of the other
points relative to V remains the same.  See 
	<A HREF="esc-trbig.gif">Figure (esc-tr)</A>
.
<P>
Move the mouse anywhere on the screen (outside the menu area), and click.
Notice
that the cylinder is moved so that V is placed at this location, and the
coordinates of the other points remain the same relative to V.
<P>
<tt>mged&gt; <em>p 0 0 0</em> <BR>mged&gt;
</tt>
<P>
This restores the solid to the original location.
<P>
<HR>

